<LegalLayout title="Text Messaging Policy" updated="January 1, 2022">
  <p>
    The Muslim American Society of Minnesota offers a mobile messaging program, "MAS MN Alerts,"
    governed by the terms below, effective January 1, 2022.
  </p>
  <h2>Enrollment</h2>
  <p>
    Join by texting "JOIN" to <a href="tel:+16514577170">651-457-7170</a>. Message and data rates
    may apply. Message frequency varies based on your activity and interaction with the program.
  </p>
  <h2>Opting out</h2>
  <p>
    You may leave the program at any time by replying "STOP," "QUIT," "END," "CANCEL,"
    "UNSUBSCRIBE," or "STOP ALL" to any message. These are the only reasonable methods of
    opting out.
  </p>
  <h2>Your responsibilities</h2>
  <p>
    Subscribers must notify MAS Minnesota before discontinuing use of their phone number.
    Failure to do so may make the subscriber responsible for costs, including attorneys' fees,
    incurred if messages reach a new holder of that number.
  </p>
  <h2>What you'll receive</h2>
  <p>
    Messages relate to MAS Minnesota's non-profit activities, including event announcements,
    account information, and organizational updates.
  </p>
  <h2>Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    MAS Minnesota does not sell, rent, loan, trade, lease, or otherwise transfer phone numbers to
    for-profit entities. Numbers may be shared with service providers necessary to deliver the
    program.
  </p>
  <h2>Disputes</h2>
  <p>
    Disputes arising from this program are resolved through binding arbitration in St. Paul,
    Minnesota, rather than class-action litigation.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
